{
  "text": "At age 30 years, the Malaise Inventory (MI) was completed by 11,106 cohort members and the GHQ-12 by 11,105. MI scores were dichotomised, as in the 1958 analyses, into 'no malaise' (77.3%, [CITATION_1] 586) or 'malaise present' (22.7%, 2,520). On the GHQ-12, 42.2% (4,682) of this sample scored more than 10.",
